{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# FightMind AI — Google Colab Fine-Tuning Guide\n","    Purpose: Fine-tune the all-MiniLM-L6-v2 embedding model on domain-specific martial arts text to maximise RAG retrieval accuracy.\n","    Runtime: Google Colab — Free T4 GPU (~45 min for 10 epochs on ~10k pairs)\n","    Cost: ₹0 / $0\n","\n","# Why Fine-Tune?\n","    Query\tBase -- model top result -- Fine-tuned top result\n","    \"How do I throw a jab?\" -- Generic punch article -- Jab technique tutorial ✅\n","    \"What is ippon in kumite?\" -- General sports scoring -- Karate kumite rules ✅\n","    \"Explain low kick\" -- Generic leg strike -- Kickboxing low kick technique ✅\n","\n","# Prerequisites (run once locally)\n","- Make sure data/processed/chunks.json exists:\n","#\n","    # Step 1 — collect raw data (if not done already)\n","    python -m src.data_collection.scraper\n","\n","    # Step 2 — preprocess into chunks\n","    python -m src.training.preprocess\n","\n","    # Verify chunks were created\n","    # Expected: data/processed/chunks.json (~10–30 MB)"],"metadata":{"id":"SwaK9Pw3qp1l"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Step-by-Step: Running on Google Colab"],"metadata":{"id":"SPJwx9EntXlC"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# 1. Open Google Colab\n","    Go to colab.research.google.com and create a new notebook.\n","\n","# 2. Select T4 GPU Runtime\n","    Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU → Save\n","\n","# 3. Mount Google Drive (to save the model)\n","    from google.colab import drive\n","    drive.mount('/content/drive')\n","\n","# 4. Upload chunks.json to Google Drive\n","- Option A — Google Drive upload (recommended — file survives session restarts)\n","\n","  \n","\n","1.   Go to drive.google.com\n","2.   Create a folder called fightmind in My Drive (or use an existing one)\n","3.   Open that folder and upload the file:\n","fightmind-model/data/processed/chunks.json from your local machine\n","4.   The file should now sit at:\n","📁 My Drive/fightmind_fine_tuned_model/chunks.json\n","\n","\n","Then in Colab, copy it to the expected location (update Step 7 accordingly):\n","#\n","    import shutil, os\n","    os.makedirs(\"data/processed\", exist_ok=True)\n","    shutil.copy(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/fightmind_fine_tuned_model/chunks.json\", \"data/processed/chunks.json\")\n","    print(\"chunks.json ready ✅\")\n","\n","- Option B — Direct Colab upload (simpler, but lost if session restarts)\n","#\n","    from google.colab import files\n","    uploaded = files.upload()   # A file picker opens → select data/processed/chunks.json\n","    # The file is saved as /content/chunks.json\n","\n","Then in Step 7, copy it:\n","#\n","    import shutil, os\n","    os.makedirs(\"data/processed\", exist_ok=True)\n","    shutil.copy(\"/content/chunks.json\", \"data/processed/chunks.json\")\n","    print(\"chunks.json ready ✅\")\n","\n","# 5. Install dependencies\n","    # accelerate is required by sentence-transformers Trainer (model.fit)\n","    !pip install sentence-transformers==3.4.1 \"accelerate>=0.26.0\" hf_xet --quiet\n","\n","# 6. Clone your repo (or upload fine_tune.py directly)\n","    # Option A — clone from GitHub (recommended)\n","    !git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/fightmind-model.git\n","    %cd fightmind-model\n","    !pip install -r requirements.txt --quiet\n","\n","    # Option B — upload fine_tune.py manually via sidebar\n","\n","# 7. Copy chunks.json to expected location\n","    import shutil, os\n","    os.makedirs(\"data/processed\", exist_ok=True)\n","\n","    # If you used Option A (Google Drive upload):\n","    shutil.copy(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/fightmind_fine_tuned_model/chunks.json\", \"data/processed/chunks.json\")\n","\n","    # If you used Option B (direct Colab upload), comment the line above and use:\n","    # shutil.copy(\"/content/chunks.json\", \"data/processed/chunks.json\")\n","\n","    print(f\"chunks.json ready ✅  size={(os.path.getsize('data/processed/chunks.json')/1024/1024):.1f} MB\")\n","\n","# 8. Run fine-tuning\n","    # Recommended settings for Colab T4 (16GB VRAM):\n","    !python -m src.training.fine_tune \\\n","        --epochs 10 \\\n","        --batch-size 32 \\\n","        --max-pairs 10000 \\\n","        --output /content/drive/MyDrive/fightmind_fine_tuned_model/model_output\n","\n","Expected output:\n","#\n","    INFO | Fine-tuning started  [pairs=8432, epochs=10, batch_size=32]\n","    Epoch 1/10: 100%|████████| 264/264 [04:12<00:00]\n","    ...\n","    INFO | Fine-tuning complete — model saved  [output=.../fightmind_fine_tuned_model/model_output]\n","\n","# 9. Download the model to your machine\n","After training completes, the model is saved to your Google Drive at:\n","MyDrive/fightmind_fine_tuned_model/model_output\n","\n","Download it and copy to your local repo:\n","#\n","    fightmind-model/\n","    └── models/\n","        └── fine_tuned/        ← copy files here\n","            ├── config.json\n","            ├── tokenizer/\n","            └── pytorch_model.bin (or model.safetensors)\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","# On any Issue\n","- Perform this action to delete current session and reconnect\n","#\n","    Runtime -> Disconnect and delete runtime"],"metadata":{"id":"JaSOVjaBtdBe"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Actual code for Colab Notebook"],"metadata":{"id":"LLqGTQ-3vKsV"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Cell 1 — Setup"],"metadata":{"id":"Hf7Lye1evTP7"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')\n","\n","!git clone https://github.com/akashpatole43/fightmind-model.git\n","\n","# Only install fine-tuning packages — don't run pip install -r requirements.txt\n","!pip install sentence-transformers==3.4.1 \"accelerate>=0.26.0\" pyyaml hf_xet --quiet"],"metadata":{"id":"joutxmsNvYcU","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773570364708,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":96765,"user":{"displayName":"Akash Pat